There has been quite the tug of war in VTK w.r.t. this forwarder.

 - Originally, the loader had forwarded its events to the importer.
 - in de1602836934 (MR#12033) (2025-03-30) it was removed as part of a bug fix.
 - In 55ef1381 (2025-09-10) it was restored, having been flagged as an
   accidental removal.
 - In 571196de4efff (2026-05-29) it was reverted referencing MR#12033.

Drake, however, depends on loader events being forwarded to the importer (where
Drake has a registered observer).

I broached this topic in VTK MR#12033 (see the link):

https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/merge_requests/12033#note_1827292

Summary:

  - The forwarder doesn't do what it promises.
  - Once an event is forwarded to *any* observer, it must be resolved by an
    observer, or not at all.
  - For any VTK user that doesn't provide an observer, all GLTF loader messages
    simply evaporated.
  - This is why forwarding was considered "defective".

Short solution:

  - When an observer is present, InvokeEvent() returns a bool indicating whether
    the event was handled.
  - Previously, the result was ignored. This change checks the result and
    falls back to printing to the output window if it wasn't handled.
  - This should robustly serve both use cases.


--- Common/Core/vtkOutputWindow.cxx
+++ Common/Core/vtkOutputWindow.cxx
@@ -107,15 +107,20 @@ void vtkOutputWindowDisplayErrorText(
 {
   std::ostringstream vtkmsg;
   vtkmsg << "ERROR: In " << fname << ", line " << lineno << "\n" << message << "\n\n";
+  vtkTypeBool dispatched = false;
   if (sourceObj && sourceObj->HasObserver(vtkCommand::ErrorEvent))
   {
-    sourceObj->InvokeEvent(vtkCommand::ErrorEvent, const_cast<char*>(vtkmsg.str().c_str()));
+    dispatched = sourceObj->InvokeEvent(vtkCommand::ErrorEvent,
+                                        const_cast<char*>(vtkmsg.str().c_str()));
   }
-  else if (auto win = vtkOutputWindow::GetInstance())
+  if (!dispatched)
   {
-    vtkLogger::Log(vtkLogger::VERBOSITY_ERROR, fname, lineno, message);
-    vtkOutputWindowPrivateAccessor helper_raii(win);
-    win->DisplayErrorText(vtkmsg.str().c_str());
+    if (auto win = vtkOutputWindow::GetInstance())
+    {
+      vtkLogger::Log(vtkLogger::VERBOSITY_ERROR, fname, lineno, message);
+      vtkOutputWindowPrivateAccessor helper_raii(win);
+      win->DisplayErrorText(vtkmsg.str().c_str());
+    }
   }
 }

